instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The framework conforms to the BIM materialization stack and relies on the Industry Foundation Classes (IFC) open interchange format for the initial model representation. Device metadata is specified using IFC property sets and GUIDs, and the service layer is exposed through Eclipse Hono, providing MQTT‑based event transport compliant with industry IoT communication standards, while Eclipse Ditto offers a device twin API compliant with open twin management specifications. Standards such as ISO 19650 for BIM deliverables and ISO 27001 for information security are adhered to. The architecture promotes interoperability across heterogeneous BIM tools, IoT protocols (e.g., MQTT, HTTP/REST), and visualization systems (e.g., Unreal Engine 5). Modular extension points support standard OSGi‑style bundles or REST interfaces, aligning with widely accepted software componentization practices."
]
